      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/35/14",
      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ رَجُلٌ رَهَنَ عِنْدَ رَجُلٍ سِوَارَيْنِ فَهَلَكَ أَحَدُهُمَا قَالَ \"يَرْجِعُ بِحَقِّهِ فِيمَا بَقِيَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4107 - Aban narrated from Ubayd ibn Zurara, who said:\n\"I asked Abu Abdullah (as) about a man who pledged two bracelets (siwarayn) as security with another man, and one of them was destroyed.\"\nImam (as) replied: \"He may reclaim his right from what remains.\""
        ]
      }
    },
